00:43:08,201 --> 00:43:10,600
I think he's a student of natural philosophy.

483
00:43:10,601 --> 00:43:17,961
That really hasn't branched out into philosophy and science yet in Dostoevsky's time, at the time of the brothers.

484
00:43:17,961 --> 00:43:33,481
So it was a study of the nature, but also of human nature, and it was what you would be naturing in, I think, at least if you were a philosopher in your interests.

485
00:43:35,081 --> 00:43:36,760
And where else?

486
00:43:39,320 --> 00:43:41,881
Okay, so much for that aspect of it.

487
00:43:44,041 --> 00:43:47,321
So we've got him now showing pride.

