00:47:23,320 --> 00:47:27,601
And they're trying to figure out what Yvonne really wants.

525
00:47:28,240 --> 00:47:32,321
And you can see it if you will keep your eyes open.

526
00:47:33,360 --> 00:47:45,841
On 42, 10 lines, 8, 2, 4, 6 lines down, Alyasha, that is he, attributed his brother's coolness at first to a difference in their age and education.

527
00:47:45,840 --> 00:47:52,801
But he also wondered whether the absence of curiosity and sympathy in Yvonne might be due to some other cause entirely unknown to him.

528
00:47:52,800 --> 00:48:02,561
He kept thinking that Yvonne was absorbed in something, something inward and important, that he was striving towards some goal, perhaps very hard to attain.

529
00:48:02,880 --> 00:48:05,521
Well, that's right, he is.

530
00:48:05,521 --> 00:48:13,041
And the goal is, you get clearer about it, on 77.

531
00:48:19,760 --> 00:48:29,441
This very elusive conversation between Sasam and Yvonne, which is very important and interesting and obscure, on 77.

532
00:48:29,440 --> 00:48:34,161
I'm going to read it starting about a third down.

533
00:48:37,681 --> 00:48:40,001
Father Zasfa asked Yvonne.

534
00:48:42,161 --> 00:48:43,281
It's complicated.

535
00:48:43,601 --> 00:48:48,801
Dostieski is sort of laying out a whole lot of his philosophy on these two pages.

