00:51:18,800 --> 00:51:22,401
For our dwelling is in the heavens, Zosima said.

578
00:51:22,400 --> 00:51:32,400
I'm going to try to convince you later that Zosima is sort of traditional kind of Christianity mixed up with Platonism, that he never quite gets it right.

579
00:51:33,201 --> 00:51:33,920
But almost.

580
00:51:33,920 --> 00:51:37,281
So here he says, so our dwelling is in the heavens.

581
00:51:37,280 --> 00:51:40,641
God grant that your heart will attain the answer on earth.

582
00:51:40,641 --> 00:51:42,240
And may God bless your path.

583
00:51:42,240 --> 00:51:45,280
So he's got his foot in both of the stories.

584
00:51:45,521 --> 00:51:50,240
He's like Kierkegaard in thinking that if you're not blissful on earth, then you've lost it.

