00:52:01,440 --> 00:52:08,081
But he also thinks in a way that Kierkegaard would never say, I think, that our dwelling is in the heavens.

588
00:52:08,081 --> 00:52:15,281
That's Plato-like, saying that we all should be and are, in a way, friends of God and can merge with God.

589
00:52:15,280 --> 00:52:19,121
So anyway, so Zosima is this interesting character.

590
00:52:19,121 --> 00:52:26,720
And whenever he reads Zasima, you have to see that he's so, so advanced, and he's made Christian love into a science, as it says in some place.

