00:52:52,121 --> 00:52:56,361
We haven't quite done the goal because it gets a little clearer what the goal is.

598
00:52:57,481 --> 00:53:01,960
This goal is in some way a kind of eternal perfection.

599
00:53:01,961 --> 00:53:07,481
And now I want to say he wants to be pure, but I don't think I should say that.

600
00:53:07,481 --> 00:53:09,400
He wants to be clean.

601
00:53:10,360 --> 00:53:11,000
Clear.

602
00:53:11,001 --> 00:53:14,601
No, clear is too much like purity.

603
00:53:14,601 --> 00:53:16,361
He wants to be clean.

604
00:53:16,360 --> 00:53:19,801
And that's the sense in which he's a Platonist.

605
00:53:19,800 --> 00:53:30,920
And if our dwelling was in heaven, then why shouldn't we just leave the earth and go and dwell in the heaven?

606
00:53:31,240 --> 00:53:37,641
And all of stuff that comes from having bodies and all of that stuff would just be left behind.

607
00:53:37,641 --> 00:53:42,440
And that's not Dostoevsky's idea, and it's not Kierkegaard's idea of the finite.

608
00:53:42,440 --> 00:53:45,881
The temporal and finite are just as important as the eternal.

609
00:53:45,880 --> 00:53:48,361
And earth is just as important as heaven.

